Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a garlic press).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British chicken breast{260%g}(diced) to the frying pan. Cook, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} to the pan and cook for a further ~{4-5%minutes} until both the chicken and bacon are golden and cooked through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the @linguine{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Stir the @finely chopped tomatoes{1}(@chopped), @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @Worcester sauce{15%ml}, @sugar{1} and @water{100%ml} into the bacon pan. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to low.

Simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Once the pasta is cooked, add to your sauce with half the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated).

Toss to coat, then season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Warm through until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @wild rocket{40%g} into a #medium bowl{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

When ready, share the bacon and chicken linguine between your bowls and sprinkle with the remaining cheese.

Serve the rocket in bowls alongside with a drizzle of the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}.

Enjoy!